  "prompt": "Can gravity slow time?",
  "response": "Yes, gravity can affect the passage of time, a phenomenon predicted by Albert Einstein's theory of general relativity. This effect is known as gravitational time dilation. According to general relativity, the stronger the gravitational field (or the closer you are to a massive object), the slower time will pass relative to an observer in a weaker gravitational field.\n\nFor example, time passes more slowly closer to the surface of a massive object like Earth compared to the further reaches of space where gravitational influence is weaker. This has been confirmed through various experiments, including precise measurements conducted with atomic clocks at different altitudes.",
